2 HOUSE BILL 358
1 (I) PROVIDES SOCCER OPPORTUNITIES FOR CHILDREN UNDER
2 THE AGE OF 18 YEARS; AND
3 (II) IS RECOGNIZED BY THE UNITED STATES SOCCER
4 FEDERATION AS A MEMBER OF THE MARYLAND STATE YOUTH SOCCER
5 ASSOCIATION.
6 (B) (1) THERE IS A SOCCER OPPORTUNITIES PROGRAM IN THE
7 DEPARTMENT.
8 (2) THE PURPOSE OF THE SOCCER OPPORTUNITIES PROGRAM IS TO
9 INCREASE OPPORTUNITIES FOR MINORITY STUDENTS TO PARTICIPATE IN SOCCER
10 IN THEIR COMMUNITIES.
11 (C) THE STATE SUPERINTENDENT SHALL DEVELOP AND ADMINISTER THE
12 SOCCER OPPORTUNITIES PROGRAM.
13 (D) (1) A YOUTH SOCCER NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION MAY SUBMIT AN
14 APPLICATION TO THE DEPARTMENT TO RECEIVE A GRANT FOR A PROGRAM THAT IS:
15 (I) IN FURTHERANCE OF THE PURPOSE OF THE SOCCER
16 OPPORTUNITIES PROGRAM; AND
17 (II) 1. COMPOSED OF AT LEAST 50% MINORITY PLAYERS; OR
18 2. COMPOSED OF AT LEAST 50% PLAYERS WHO QUALIFY
19 TO RECEIVE FREE LUNCH UNDER THE NATIONAL SCHOOL LUNCH PROGRAM.
20 (2) AN APPLICATION SHALL INCLUDE:
21 (I) A DESCRIPTION OF THE SCOPE AND PURPOSE OF THE
22 PROGRAM;
23 (II) A BUSINESS PLAN THAT INCLUDES THE ESTIMATED TOTAL
24 COST OF THE PROGRAM; AND
25 (III) ANY OTHER INFORMATION REQUIRED BY THE
26 DEPARTMENT.
27 (E) IN AWARDING A GRANT UNDER THE SOCCER OPPORTUNITIES
28 PROGRAM, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:

HOUSE BILL 358 3
1 (1) REQUIRE THE GRANTEE TO PROVIDE MATCHING FUNDS FROM
2 ANY COMBINATION OF FEDERAL, COUNTY, MUNICIPAL, OR PRIVATE SOURCES; AND
3 (2) ENSURE THAT THE GRANT DOES NOT EXCEED 50% OF THE TOTAL
4 ANNUAL COST OF THE GRANTEE’S PROGRAM.
5 (F) THE STATE SUPERINTENDENT OR THE STATE SUPERINTENDENT’S
6 DESIGNEE SHALL:
7 (1) REVIEW GRANT APPLICATIONS SUBMITTED IN ACCORDANCE
8 WITH SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION; AND
9 (2) TO THE EXTENT FUNDS ARE AVAILABLE, PROVIDE GRANTS TO
10 YOUTH SOCCER NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS THAT MEET THE REQUIREMENTS FOR
11 A GRANT UNDER THIS SECTION.
12 (G) FOR FISCAL YEARS 2027, 2028, AND 2029, THE GOVERNOR SHALL
13 INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF AT LEAST $100,000
14 FOR THE SOCCER OPPORTUNITIES PROGRAM.
15 (H) THE STATE SUPERINTENDENT SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY
16 OUT THIS SECTION.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
18 1, 2025.

